summary: re: roman azi asking if crowley was still a demon.  how do you think aziraphale would have reacted had crowley *not* been a...
question: re: roman azi asking if crowley was still a demon.  how do you think aziraphale would have reacted had crowley *not* been a demon anymore?
answer:
Oh gosh…

I think he probably would have been less reluctant to be friends with him, and he may have even been more willing to admit he loved him. Certainly Heaven would be more willing to accept two angels falling in love than an angel and a demon, even if one of those angels had been a demon for a few thousand years. At least, that’s how Aziraphale would likely perceive it.
